Step 18 : Calculating the mode variables

find_mode <- function(x)
{
  u <- unique(x)
  tab <- tabulate(match(x,u))
  u[tab == max(tab)]
}

  1. Check for the numeric variables
numeric_dataset <- function(Dataset){
nums <- sapply(Dataset, is.numeric)
return(Dataset[ , nums])
  }
iris_num <- numeric_dataset(indata)
str(iris_num)

Step 30 : Summary of insights analysis

From the above analysis, Setosa has lots of fluctuations in it’s dimensions as its sepal width is considered highest among all other species, however less among other species when compared in case of petal length & width and sepal length.Virginica also has lots of fluctuations in its’s dimensions , It is considered highest among 3 categories which are sepal length, petal length and petal width and constant in sepal width.Vesrsicolor dimensions looks better when compared with other two, much fluctuations are not seen.
